WEBVTT

00:03:59.484 --> 00:04:01.376
In both cases,

00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:05.639
"whatever it takes" meant
trillions of dollars more

00:04:05.663 --> 00:04:08.891
in money-printing policies
that continue today.

00:04:09.334 --> 00:04:11.122
What this shows

00:04:11.146 --> 00:04:14.912
is that when faced
with some global challenges,

00:04:16.062 --> 00:04:20.707
policy makers are able to act
collectively, with urgency,

00:04:20.731 --> 00:04:26.861
and run the risks of unconventional
policies like money printing.

00:04:27.509 --> 00:04:31.560
So, let's go back
to that original question: